trigger.description: MySQL Service - Slave SQL thread stopped
trigger.comments: SQL thread has stopped. This is usually because it cannot apply a SQL statement received from the master.

Checks of MySQL Server is up and running. Raises a alert if does not provide a measue for 300 seconds or the uptime does not change anymore (in this case mysql_extend was not able to update the value).

Reserved disk space for database emergency situations. If disk space is exceeded, you can delete this file to gain space for proper shutdown.
Typically create a file using the following command: dd if=/dev/zero of={$DB_PART}/FEDERAL_ADMIN_RESERVE_BANK count=512 bs=1M
Partition is running out of space. Please increase volume size, delete unnecessary files and inform application owner.
